<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-23T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-23T04:00:00-05:00" n="237" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 Nelson, Bert N./14:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-23T17:00:00+08:00">October 23, 1930—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>98. The following telegram has been sent to the Legation: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“October 23, 5 p.m. I sent another telegram to General Ho
                                    Yingchin at Chengchow yesterday urging upon him the necessity of
                                    obtaining immediate release of Reverend Nelso. I suggested also
                                        <pb facs="0302" n="204" xml:id="pg_204"/> that he send a
                                    special representative to Kwangshan to push plans for release.
                                    Have made similar representations to General Ho Chen-chun
                                    here.</p>
                                <p>Repeated to Department.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>